# Image Lazy Loading Standard

All images in this project MUST use native browser lazy loading for performance optimization.

## Required Attribute

Add `loading="lazy"` to all `<img>` elements:

```tsx
<img
  src={imageSrc}
  alt="Description"
  loading="lazy"
  className="..."
/>
```

## Exception

The **hero image** on the homepage (`/`) should NOT use lazy loading to preserve optimal Largest Contentful Paint (LCP) performance. This is the only above-the-fold critical image.

## Benefits

- Reduces initial page load time
- Defers off-screen image loading until user scrolls
- Native browser support (no JavaScript required)
- Improves Core Web Vitals scores
